 configure the task named “generateDynamicAccessReport.” I wonder if enabling that task to false would be necessary, but it's unclear at this point. Let me explore this further.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Checking class loading and test order**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how `Class.forName` connects only if the static random is null. The JUnit order property seemingly uses `$` in resource. It's interesting to consider if the class order is running by default without loading resources. Did it run first? I might need to check the test order, possibly reviewing XML timestamps to get a clearer view of this situation. There’s a lot to unravel here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_o1BnWr5y1Q6gD2XewZAXJmtO|fc_0270f4b9bb8643fe0169fba1f328f48191b86aecf7834940ff", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "for f in tests/src/com.jcraft/jsch/0.1.27/build/test-results/test/TEST-*.xml; do stat -c '%y %n' \"$f\"; done | sort"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1427, "output": 1573, "cacheRead": 74752, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 77752, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778098649979, "responseId": "resp_0270f4b9bb8643fe0169fba1db28bc8191819609a7b6e74b64"}}
